data.title: Great Appetizers
data.text: We had very good appetizers after a very long day. My hubby enjoyed the oysters and had the clam chowder which was very good. Stop by for great food.

data.title: Teeny martinis
data.text: We ordered martinis with our meals and they were much smaller than one expects for this drink. Not big enough to get either of us tipsy! We wanted another but not at the price they charge. If you are going to charge premium price, please provide a premium volume.  Good olives though... and nice server, and good food but we won't be back.

data.title: Great Local Food
data.text: We had a group of 6-7 people stop by on the first night of our trip to San Diego... we were looking for a local place with great seafood that wasn't too stuffy and our hotel concierge pointed us to Spike Africa's. Great choice. Low-key atmosphere but top-notch seafood dishes. I ended up with the grilled swordfish and a tasty jalapeno tarter sauce on the side. The ceviche app was also tasty.

data.title: Amazing Food, Friendly Staff
data.text: Walking around SD all day was exhausting and we wanted to have a nice seafood dinner.  The doorman at our hotel suggested this restaurant.  We made reservations for 830pm thinking we needed one since it was a Saturday night, but according to the hostess, the crowd usually comes earlier for dinner.  The food was succulent and fresh.  We ordered shrimp cocktain and the oysters of the day.  For our entree, he had the grilled swordfish and I had the macadia nut crusted mahi.  Sharing our entree, we both got a taste of how well both fish were seasoned and its freshness.  It didn't have that "fishy" smell.  The staff was informative with their recommendation for the drinks. Although my friend was not fond of the Anchor because it was too citrusy for his palate, it was made very strong.  For dessert, we checked in on yelp and was given the butterscotch pudding.  At this point, I was full from meal and tasted a bit of the pudding.  The rock sea salt added enhanced the flavor of the pudding.  I highly recommend this Spike Africa for a fresh seafood experience.

data.title: Amazing Oysters!
data.text: Super friendly staff! Oysters thick and meaty and if you go at happy hour between $1 and $1.50 each! Amazing! Loved it here!

data.title: Delectable Saturday Lunch
data.text: We were in downtown San Diego at Horton Plaza for an event and wanted a 2 PM Saturday lunch. Service was prompt and friendly. Two of us shared the Blackened Mahi Fish Tacos and a small Caesar Salad. The food was delectable, perfectly seasoned. We'll be back.

data.title: Great Fish Stew
data.text: Had lunch special today -- Fish Stew and salad. Perfect for a rare rainy day in downtown San Diego. Great service and food. Highly recommend.

data.title: outstanding and we'll go back!
data.text: We finally stopped in since we live locally and loved the drinks and the food.  The oysters were fresh and tasty and the beer cheese and bean dip was good.  The garlic bread was excellent, too!  We only had appetizers but based on those and the quality and value of the food, I imagine everything else is good, too.  The fish and chips that were passing by on their way to other customers looked excellent - next time!

data.title: DEFINITELY OVER-PRICED AND OVER-RATED – GO ELSEWHERE
data.text: Attracted by favorable reviews, we joined the crowd for happy hour on a Sunday afternoon. From the happy hour menu, we ordered beer ($5), white wine ($8), the Solo Mahi Nachos ($8), and Pork Street Tacos ($2). The restaurant and bar were crowded so we sat outside in a tiny sidewalk patio. Our disappointment started when we had to wait “awhile” to place our drink order. While waiting for the drinks to arrive we order the food. We waited and waited. Finally, the Pork Street Tacos (below average) arrived, but no drinks. Then the Solo Mahi Nachos (small) arrived, but no drinks. Finally, the drinks arrived. We complained that the service was terrible, and our waitress said that service is slow during happy hour. Please do yourself a favor and go somewhere else for your happy hour—like the Field Irish Pub, just around the corner on 5th Avenue.

data.title: Natalie was great and the food delicious.
data.text:
The server, Natalie, really made our special celebration memorable.  The food was delicious and the recommendations spot on.
This is a solid great find.

data.title: Recommended from a local.....
data.text: I visited Spike Africa's in August 2016 based on a recommendation from a local, and I was really impressed. I had the mustard glazed salmon based on another recommendation from the wait staff and was absolutely blown away. This was one of the best meals I had during my week while visiting San Diego. I would absolutely go back and certainly recommend this to anyone. I arrived a bit late on the night of my visit and sat at the bar. The restaurant has outside seating, but wasn't able to take advantage of it this night.

data.title: Totally Unexpected
data.text: I've passed by this restaurant many times and never thought to stop in. That was until my fiancé suggested we go. What an experience! We went on a Monday during happy hour and I thought that would spell out a recipe for long waits and just okay food. We were able to walk right in an pick a seat on the outside patio(which I suggest you do on a nice day). Our server was one of the best in downtown, always there for refills and asking if we needed anything. He was spot on everything! The food was hot and very fresh when brought to our table.  In my opinion the fish and chips beats Anthony's Fish Grotto on Harbor.

data.title: Great price oysters
data.text:
There are happy hours from 3 to 6 pm when you can get oysters for half price.  My favourite Washington ones were 1.5 dollars each: fat, juicy, creamy. 
Lobster roll was quite rich as well.

data.title: eating good
data.text: Was great !! Staff was nice and friendly... Food was good, not costly, and the atmosphere was comfortable.  I would come back and tell others about this restaurant.

data.title: Pricy but well worth it
data.text: We stumbled upon this place by chance. It has all the trimmings of high-end seafood place included a daily menu of fresh catches. We tried 3 different things - 2 from the daily menu were amongst the best seafood I've tried in US, the third - fish & chips was pretty good but huge and the leftovers (2/3 of the portion) were rubbery the next day. The main courses range from $30 to $50 so it's not a daily eatery but we'll be back given a chance. My son ordered sushi-grade tuna with a sauce that was familiar to him. the waiter said she'll bring it along with another one that was best for this choice (needless to say she turned out to be right) - that was a very nice touch. The drinks were good but not as spectacular as the food.

data.title: Spike Africa's Great Sunday Night Supper
data.text: Sunday night is a time for family and comfort food so when you are on the road it is wonderful to find a hometown place where they treat you like family and feed you special guests. The serving team and manager were all friendly and attentive. The rustic chic decor and upbeat background music said make yourself at home. We started with the ceviche, chowed down on the fish and chips and roasted Brussels. Our land lubber daughter was more than happy with her pork chop. Instead of the usual after dinner mints they bring salt water taffy with the check!

data.title: Great seafood
data.text:
Traveling to San Diego on business the hotel recommended this place for seafood. Outstanding! Great service and relaxed environment. Ate dinner at the bar and it was really good. 
Had the Macadamia nut crusted Mahi Mahi. Light and fresh.

data.title: A good menu variety
data.text: We went here for dinner and tried a few different appetizers from their menu- Crispy Brussels, Solo Nachos and Ceviche- all of them were delicious! We were not as impressed with all the main courses we received. The Rockfish was not very appealing and the portion was rather small. The Hibiscus Sangria was very good and paired well with the Lobster Roll.

data.title: Wonderful fish.  Great happy hour
data.text: We ended up going here twice during our visit.  The rock fish was wonderful.  Less of a fan of yellow tail but it was prepared well. Ginger sauce was perfect.  Great happy hour specials.  Guac is good.

data.title: Fabulous spot
data.text: There were 11 of us in three generations. Our server manage to keep all our orders straight, even though we kept changing seats. All our entrees were excellent and we could not believe how fast they came.
